data.title: The Prime Minister leaves for the Kingdom of Denmark on a working visit
data.text:
Prime Minister Nikol Pashinyan left for the Kingdom of Denmark on a working visit.

The Prime Minister will participate in the "Copenhagen Democracy Summit" on May 14. Within the framework of the summit, Nikol Pashinyan will take part in the discussion "From the frontline: Armenia's defense of democracy".

In the sidelines of the visit, meetings with the Prime Minister of the Kingdom of Denmark Mrs. Mette Frederiksen, Speaker of the Danish Parliament Folketing SÃ¸ren Gade, founder of the summit and founder of the international political consulting organization "Rasmussen Global" Anders Fogh Rasmussen are also scheduled.
